'''真人圖書館'''（{{lang-en|The Human Library}}）是一个国际性组织和运动，2000年1月发端于[[丹麦|丹麦]][[哥本哈根|哥本哈根]]，它旨在促进人们与平时不会遇到的人对话来消除隔阂。该组织学习图书馆借书的方法来“借出”真人，他们都是在日常生活中遭受到偏见或歧视者，如[[艾滋病|艾滋病]]患者、[[变性人|变性人]]、難民、戒酒者等<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-07-09|title=The Human Library Organisation replaces pages with people|url=https://www.economist.com/prospero/2017/11/03/the-human-library-organisation-replaces-pages-with-people|newspaper=The Economist|archive-date=2020-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200808100929/https://www.economist.com/prospero/2017/11/03/the-human-library-organisation-replaces-pages-with-people|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first1=Mark|last1=Rice-Oxley|accessdate=2018-07-09|title=My day as Depression, a book at the Human Library|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/shortcuts/2012/apr/08/depression-book-human-library|date=8 April 2012|website=The Guardian|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710010228/https://www.theguardian.com/society/shortcuts/2012/apr/08/depression-book-human-library|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-07-09|title=The best way to preserve the Welfare State is to reinvent it|url=https://www.bigissue.com/latest/john-bird-the-best-way-to-preserve-the-welfare-state-is-to-reinvent-it/|newspaper=The Big Issue|date=9 July 2018|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710011022/https://www.bigissue.com/latest/john-bird-the-best-way-to-preserve-the-welfare-state-is-to-reinvent-it/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。“借入”这些人的市民可以向他们提问来了解他们，同时消除自己的偏见<ref name="wellcome">{{cite news|accessdate=2018-07-09|title=Human Library|url=https://wellcomecollection.org/events/human-library-0|date=18 August 2016|website=Wellcome Collection|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709153904/https://wellcomecollection.org/events/human-library-0|archive-date=2018-07-09|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=Shoaff2016>{{cite web|url=http://www.upworthy.com/check-out-a-human-library-where-you-borrow-people-instead-of-books|title=Check out a human library, where you borrow people instead of books.|last=Shoaff|first=Morgan|website=UpWorthy|publisher=Cloud Tiger Media|date=18 February 2016|access-date=26 April 2017|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226040750/https://www.upworthy.com/check-out-a-human-library-where-you-borrow-people-instead-of-books|dead-url=no}}</ref>。目前，真人圖書館活动已在80余个国家展开，一些地区已建立了实体的真人图书馆，但大部分地区的真人图书馆仅是以定期活动的形式举行<ref name="rd">{{cite news|accessdate=2018-07-09|title=The Human Library: Where the "Books" are People|url=https://www.rd.com/culture/human-library/|newspaper=Reader's Digest|date=2 October 2017|first=Meghan|last=Jones|archive-date=2020-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417094247/https://www.rd.com/culture/human-library/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-07-09|title=Shropshire Libraries to host Human Library events to challenge stigma|url=http://shropshire.gov.uk/news/2017/12/human-library-events/|newspaper=Shropshire Council Newsroom|date=7 December 2017|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710040646/http://shropshire.gov.uk/news/2017/12/human-library-events/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2005年开始，许多国家的图书馆开始举办此类活动。第一家常驻的真人图书馆2006年在[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]][[利斯莫尔_(新南威尔士州)|利斯莫尔]]成立<ref name=Peveto2017>{{cite web|last1=Peveto|first1=Kyle|title=Human Library connects the inquisitive with 'living books'|url=http://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/entertainment_life/article_d5b65a9a-2610-11e7-9246-03aa29b3ef61.html|website=The Advocate|accessdate=26 April 2017|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710101901/https://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/entertainment_life/article_d5b65a9a-2610-11e7-9246-03aa29b3ef61.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2008年10月，真人图书馆首次在美国举办，在场共有14本“图书”可供借阅，内容包括[[裸体主义|裸体主义]]者、[[佛教徒|佛教徒]]、[[素食主义|素食主义]]者、知名出版家、[[瓦哈卡|瓦哈卡]]美国人、无家可归的妇女等等，每本书可出借30分钟<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ixueshu.com/document/fec950e8d9bcac1e318947a18e7f9386.html |title=开发读者知识资源的新模式:真人图书馆_爱学术 |access-date=2018-08-05 |archive-date=2018-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805083007/https://www.ixueshu.com/document/fec950e8d9bcac1e318947a18e7f9386.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==衍伸==
真人图书馆最初的目标群体主要是社会边缘人群和弱势群体，而在一些地区（如[[中华人民共和国|中国]]）它被衍生为一种面对面沟通交流的知识阅读方式与载体<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.wanfangdata.com.cn/details/detail.do?_type=perio&id=ddkg201708020 |title=真人图书馆. 当代矿工, 2017(6). |access-date=2018-08-05 |archive-date=2018-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805084248/http://www.wanfangdata.com.cn/details/detail.do?_type=perio&id=ddkg201708020 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ixueshu.com/document/f5dc89ea17b058ef318947a18e7f9386.html |title=凌美秀. 真人图书馆,还能走多远. 高校图书馆工作, 2013, 33(4):94-96. |access-date=2018-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805085946/https://www.ixueshu.com/document/f5dc89ea17b058ef318947a18e7f9386.html |archive-date=2018-08-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ixueshu.com/document/41d6b74d568a08cf318947a18e7f9386.html |title=程水英. 真人图书馆发展过程探析. 新世纪图书馆, 2011(9):53-54. |access-date=2018-08-05 |archive-date=2018-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805112553/https://www.ixueshu.com/document/41d6b74d568a08cf318947a18e7f9386.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2008年，“真人图书馆”活动首次被引入中国，[[上海交通大学|上海交通大学]]、[[石家庄学院|石家庄学院]]、[[大连医科大学|大连医科大学]]、[[同济大学|同济大学]]等大学先后开展了真人图书馆借阅活动，“图书”涉及[[留学|留学]]、[[考研|考研]]、工作、海外生活等领域<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ixueshu.com/document/951cdc4b6adc83db318947a18e7f9386.html |title=张真一. 真人图书馆在我国的发展瓶颈与对策. 图书与情报, 2014(4):132-135. |access-date=2018-08-05 |archive-date=2018-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805082932/https://www.ixueshu.com/document/951cdc4b6adc83db318947a18e7f9386.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 香港的社福机构，也把“真人图书馆”应用于推广精神健康。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=关 |first=志健 |date=2020 |title=A Qualitative Inquiry into the Human Library Approach: Facilitating Social Inclusion and Promoting Recovery |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7246815/ |journal=international journal of environmental research and public health}}</ref>

